keywords: ["Transformers", "Attention Mechanism", "Sparsity", "LLM Optimization", "CUDA Kernels"]
abstract: |
  The quadratic complexity of the standard self-attention mechanism remains a 
  significant bottleneck for processing long sequences in Large Language Models (LLMs). 
  This paper proposes a novel sparse attention kernel that leverages block-level 
  sparsity to reduce memory overhead and latency. Our approach achieves a 40% 
  speedup on sequences of 32k tokens while maintaining 98% of the model's 
  perplexity on standard benchmarks.
